If you deserve more…ACT LIKE IT!

Comparison mode, other peoples opinions/projections and social media will have you questioning Gods flawless work. Lemme tell you….comparison is truly the thief of joy. I almost lost it all entertaining the demon called “comparison”…..
Whewww! Talk about self sabotage! Talk about not feeling worthy….

It was hard for me to accept that my poor luck in relationships was a manifestation of a deep absence. It was even harder to accept that my relationships were a manifestation of my own lack of self love and self worth. 

Romantic love couldn’t truly blossom in my life until I learned  Self Love! 

Romantic Love will really make you get your shit together! I realized the love my husband was showing me was divine because it was a love that was holding me accountable. I surrendered when I felt  safe to love and be loved…
( HONESTLY CREATES SECURITY)
I recognized that it was my responsibility to transmute and transcend everything that was inhibiting me from embracing love. & I did! 

Partnership is not easy! It’s work! It’s an energetic labor! It’s an emotional labor. It’s a physical labor and it is a spiritual undertaking!  Strong partnership requires time, patience and innerstanding to sustain! Too often I see folks quitting on DIVINE love. I was a quitter too when I didn’t feel truly worthy…..

I’m thankful for love…for showing me things about myself that I didn’t have the fortitude yet to see! 

I could go on and on about this topic. 

So let this post serve as an invitation to keep going. To recommit yourself and to try a little harder at love…and at life !

There’s a particular energy in those hills….if you’ve been there you know! It’s really a special place in the city. Black Mecca vibes! It’s one of the only areas in the city where you can get a view of the entire city….hence the name “view park”
I always felt like the people from my neighborhood where a little more tapped into source than the rest of the LA…idk maybe it’s hometown admiration but I truly feel like there’s something there. My dad used to always call west LA “Ancient Egypt”…. I wish he was alive to explain his theory….anyway that cross on the side of the 101 freeway ALWAYS catches my attention. She spent a small fortune trying to prove that Osiris tomb was under the mountain and scientist did in fact confirm that there was a tomb like structure buried beneath the mountain….makes me think about pyramid lake too…wonder what’s under there….I gotta do some studying but I think there are star similarities in the charts of Egyptian natives and LA natives specifically those born in 90943…
